      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "al",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1475294164,
      "version": 9,
      "versionNonce": 2072147820,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1772033987978,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open-source standard for connecting AI applications to external systems.\nUsing MCP, AI applications like Claude or ChatGPT can connect to data sources (e.g. local files, databases),\n tools (e.g. search engines, calculators) and workflows (e.g. specialized prompts)—enabling them to access \nkey information and perform tasks. Think of MCP like a USB-C port for AI applications. Just as USB-C provides\n a standardized way to connect electronic devices, MCP provides a standardized way to connect AI applications\n to external systems.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open-source standard for connecting AI applications to external systems.\nUsing MCP, AI applications like Claude or ChatGPT can connect to data sources (e.g. local files, databases),\n tools (e.g. search engines, calculators) and workflows (e.g. specialized prompts)—enabling them to access \nkey information and perform tasks. Think of MCP like a USB-C port for AI applications. Just as USB-C provides\n a standardized way to connect electronic devices, MCP provides a standardized way to connect AI applications\n to external systems.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
